NSAIDs, including naproxen, can cause serious skin adverse reactions such as exfoliative dermatitis, Stevens-Johnson Syndrome (SJS), and toxic epidermal necrolysis (TEN), which can be fatal. These serious events may occur without warning. Inform patients about the signs and symptoms of serious skin reactions, and to discontinue the use of naproxen sodium at the first appearance of skin rash or any other sign of hypersensitivity. Naproxen sodium is contraindicated in patients with previous serious skin reactions to NSAIDs [see Contraindications 


                              (4)
                           ].
